            <span class="readable">&ldquo;I have often wondered what was the source of her beauty, her radiance. Itâs not the size of oneâs nose, the color of oneâs skin, the shape of oneâs lips or eyes that make one beautiful or ugly. So what is it? Can you, as a woman, tell me? <br />I shook my head. <br />I will tell you: Itâs love. Love makes us beautiful. Do you know a single person who loves and is loved, who is loved unconditionally and who, at the same time, is ugly? Thereâs no need to ponder the question. There is no such person.&rdquo;</span>
